Package it.unipr.sowide.actodes.service.group.content

Class Cancel

java.lang.Object
it.unipr.sowide.actodes.service.group.content.Cancel
All Implemented Interfaces:
Request, Group, Serializable
public final class Cancel
extends Object
implements Group
The Cancel class defines a task request asking an actor space service provider to cancel a member from a group. Note that the actor that registered the group can remove one or more actors from the group; the other actors can only remove themselves. Moreover, the operation also fails if the provider service does not manage a group with such a name. Its answer contains either a Done or an Error object.
See Also:
Done, Error, Serialized Form

  • Constructor Details

    • Cancel

      public Cancel​(String n, Role r)
      Class constructor.
      Parameters:
      n - the group name.
      r - the role of the actor. Creates an object that an actor can use for removing itself or an its role from a group (i.e., if an actor acts with both the publisher and the subscriber roles, then it can decide to maintain one of the two roles in the group).

    • Cancel

      public Cancel​(String n, Role r, Reference... a)
      Class constructor.
      Parameters:
      n - the group name.
      r - the role of the actors.
      a - the references of the actors. Creates an object that the actor that creates the group can use for removing a set of actors or a their role from a group (i.e., if some of such actors act with both the publisher and the subscriber roles, then they can maintain one of the two roles in the group).
